{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_dc59c88aae744d31935292ae","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task: Admin Config Persistence + Route Wiring\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\tPort admin config CRUD from Python to TypeScript and wire the get-config/set-config routes to use real GCS persistence instead of mock data.\n5\t\n6\t## Context\n7\tThe legacy admin config is a JSON file in GCS (`config/admin_config.json`). Admin users can read/write settings (whitelisted users, etc.) through the settings page. The TS app currently returns `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` from `mock-data.ts`. This task replaces that with real GCS reads/writes.\n8\t\n9\t## Read These Files First\n10\t1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 41-80) — `set_admin_config()` and `get_raw_admin_config()` methods to port\n11\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/admin/get-config/route.ts` (full file) — currently imports `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA`\n12\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/admin/set-config/route.ts` (full file) — if it exists, check current implementation\n13\t4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `writeJson()` for persistence\n14\t5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdminForPage()` for auth\n15\t6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/mock-data.ts` (lines 383-396) — `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` shape to match\n16\t\n17\t## Changes Required\n18\t\n19\t### 1. Create `app/utils/admin-config.ts`\n20\t\n21\t```typescript\n22\timport { readJson, writeJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n23\t\n24\texport async function getAdminConfig(): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n25\t  try {\n26\t    const config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n27\t    return (config.raw_config as Record<string, unknown>) || {};\n28\t  } catch {\n29\t    // File not found — return empty config (matching legacy admin.py:78-80)\n30\t    return {};\n31\t  }\n32\t}\n33\t\n34\texport async function setAdminConfig(configParams: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> {\n35\t  // Read existing config\n36\t  let config: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n37\t  try {\n38\t    config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n39\t  } catch {\n40\t    // File not found — start fresh\n41\t  }\n42\t\n43\t  config.raw_config = configParams;\n44\t\n45\t  // Extract whitelisted user emails (matching legacy admin.py:47-53)\n46\t  const whitelistedEmails: string[] = [];\n47\t  const whitelistedUsers = configParams.i_whitelisted_user;\n48\t  if (Array.isArray(whitelistedUsers)) {\n49\t    for (const user of whitelistedUsers) {\n50\t      if (user && typeof user === 'object' && 'i_whitelisted_user_email' in user) {\n51\t        const email = (user as Record<string, unknown>).i_whitelisted_user_email;\n52\t        if (typeof email === 'string') {\n53\t          whitelistedEmails.push(email.trim().toLowerCase());\n54\t        }\n55\t      }\n56\t    }\n57\t  }\n58\t  config.whitelisted_user_emails = whitelistedEmails;\n59\t\n60\t  await writeJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG, config);\n61\t}\n62\t```\n63\t\n64\t### 2. Modify `app/api/admin/admin/get-config/route.ts`\n65\t\n66\tReplace the entire file:\n67\t```typescript\n68\timport { getAdminConfig } from '../../../../utils/admin-config';\n69\timport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n70\t\n71\texport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n72\t  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'admin_settings.html');\n73\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n74\t\n75\t  const config = await getAdminConfig();\n76\t  // CRITICAL: keep text/plain — client JS does JSON.parse(data)\n77\t  return new Response(JSON.stringify(config), {\n78\t    headers: { 'content-type': 'text/plain' },\n79\t  });\n80\t}\n81\t```\n82\t\n83\t### 3. Modify `app/api/admin/admin/set-config/route.ts`\n84\t\n85\tReplace or create. **IMPORTANT:** The settings page uses jQuery `$.post()` which sends `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` data (see `settings/render.ts:143-146`), NOT JSON. The `config_params` field is a JSON string inside a form field.\n86\t\n87\t```typescript\n88\timport { setAdminConfig } from '../../../../utils/admin-config';\n89\timport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n90\t\n91\texport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n92\t  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'admin_settings.html');\n93\t  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n94\t\n95\t  // Settings page sends form-urlencoded via jQuery $.post(), not JSON\n96\t  const contentType = request.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n97\t  let configParams: Record<string, unknown>;\n98\t\n99\t  if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {\n100\t    const body = await request.json() as Record<string, unknown>;\n101\t    configParams = body.config_params as Record<string, unknown>;\n102\t  } else {\n103\t    // Form-urlencoded: config_params is a JSON string field\n104\t    const formData = await request.formData();\n105\t    const raw = formData.get('config_params');\n106\t    if (typeof raw !== 'string') {\n107\t      return Response.json({ error: 'config_params required' }, { status: 400 });\n108\t    }\n109\t    configParams = JSON.parse(raw) as Record<string, unknown>;\n110\t  }\n111\t\n112\t  if (!configParams || typeof configParams !== 'object') {\n113\t    return Response.json({ error: 'config_params must be an object' }, { status: 400 });\n114\t  }\n115\t\n116\t  await setAdminConfig(configParams);\n117\t  return Response.json({ ok: true });\n118\t}\n119\t```\n120\t\n121\t## Constraints\n122\t- Keep `text/plain` content-type on get-config response (client JS double-parses)\n123\t- Do NOT modify `mock-data.ts` yet — other routes still depend on it\n124\t- Do NOT modify any admin HTML page routes — only the data API routes\n125\t- `getAdminConfig()` returns `raw_config` content, matching what legacy's `get_raw_admin_config()` returns (the inner config, not the wrapper)\n126\t\n127\t## Verification\n128\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n129\t\n130\t## Completion\n131\t- Commit with message: `feat: port admin config CRUD with GCS persistence`\n132\t- Report: files changed, verification result\n133\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"091c07a1-d14b-4cea-92df-7688c08d19fa","uuid":"f9e95693-731d-4751-890c-941a93f68baa","timestamp":"2026-04-06T10:25:28.199Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-3-admin-config.md","content":"# Task: Admin Config Persistence + Route Wiring\n\n## Goal\nPort admin config CRUD from Python to TypeScript and wire the get-config/set-config routes to use real GCS persistence instead of mock data.\n\n## Context\nThe legacy admin config is a JSON file in GCS (`config/admin_config.json`). Admin users can read/write settings (whitelisted users, etc.) through the settings page. The TS app currently returns `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` from `mock-data.ts`. This task replaces that with real GCS reads/writes.\n\n## Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/admin.py` (lines 41-80) — `set_admin_config()` and `get_raw_admin_config()` methods to port\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/admin/get-config/route.ts` (full file) — currently imports `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA`\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/admin/set-config/route.ts` (full file) — if it exists, check current implementation\n4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `writeJson()` for persistence\n5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/auth-middleware.ts` — `requireAdminForPage()` for auth\n6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/mock-data.ts` (lines 383-396) — `MOCK_SETTINGS_DATA` shape to match\n\n## Changes Required\n\n### 1. Create `app/utils/admin-config.ts`\n\n```typescript\nimport { readJson, writeJson, GCS_PATHS } from './gcs';\n\nexport async function getAdminConfig(): Promise<Record<string, unknown>> {\n  try {\n    const config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n    return (config.raw_config as Record<string, unknown>) || {};\n  } catch {\n    // File not found — return empty config (matching legacy admin.py:78-80)\n    return {};\n  }\n}\n\nexport async function setAdminConfig(configParams: Record<string, unknown>): Promise<void> {\n  // Read existing config\n  let config: Record<string, unknown> = {};\n  try {\n    config = await readJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  } catch {\n    // File not found — start fresh\n  }\n\n  config.raw_config = configParams;\n\n  // Extract whitelisted user emails (matching legacy admin.py:47-53)\n  const whitelistedEmails: string[] = [];\n  const whitelistedUsers = configParams.i_whitelisted_user;\n  if (Array.isArray(whitelistedUsers)) {\n    for (const user of whitelistedUsers) {\n      if (user && typeof user === 'object' && 'i_whitelisted_user_email' in user) {\n        const email = (user as Record<string, unknown>).i_whitelisted_user_email;\n        if (typeof email === 'string') {\n          whitelistedEmails.push(email.trim().toLowerCase());\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n  config.whitelisted_user_emails = whitelistedEmails;\n\n  await writeJson(GCS_PATHS.ADMIN_CONFIG, config);\n}\n```\n\n### 2. Modify `app/api/admin/admin/get-config/route.ts`\n\nReplace the entire file:\n```typescript\nimport { getAdminConfig } from '../../../../utils/admin-config';\nimport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n\nexport async function GET(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'admin_settings.html');\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  const config = await getAdminConfig();\n  // CRITICAL: keep text/plain — client JS does JSON.parse(data)\n  return new Response(JSON.stringify(config), {\n    headers: { 'content-type': 'text/plain' },\n  });\n}\n```\n\n### 3. Modify `app/api/admin/admin/set-config/route.ts`\n\nReplace or create. **IMPORTANT:** The settings page uses jQuery `$.post()` which sends `application/x-www-form-urlencoded` data (see `settings/render.ts:143-146`), NOT JSON. The `config_params` field is a JSON string inside a form field.\n\n```typescript\nimport { setAdminConfig } from '../../../../utils/admin-config';\nimport { requireAdminForPage } from '../../../../utils/auth-middleware';\n\nexport async function POST(request: Request): Promise<Response> {\n  const auth = await requireAdminForPage(request, 'admin_settings.html');\n  if (auth instanceof Response) return auth;\n\n  // Settings page sends form-urlencoded via jQuery $.post(), not JSON\n  const contentType = request.headers.get('content-type') || '';\n  let configParams: Record<string, unknown>;\n\n  if (contentType.includes('application/json')) {\n    const body = await request.json() as Record<string, unknown>;\n    configParams = body.config_params as Record<string, unknown>;\n  } else {\n    // Form-urlencoded: config_params is a JSON string field\n    const formData = await request.formData();\n    const raw = formData.get('config_params');\n    if (typeof raw !== 'string') {\n      return Response.json({ error: 'config_params required' }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n    configParams = JSON.parse(raw) as Record<string, unknown>;\n  }\n\n  if (!configParams || typeof configParams !== 'object') {\n    return Response.json({ error: 'config_params must be an object' }, { status: 400 });\n  }\n\n  await setAdminConfig(configParams);\n  return Response.json({ ok: true });\n}\n```\n\n## Constraints\n- Keep `text/plain` content-type on get-config response (client JS double-parses)\n- Do NOT modify `mock-data.ts` yet — other routes still depend on it\n- Do NOT modify any admin HTML page routes — only the data API routes\n- `getAdminConfig()` returns `raw_config` content, matching what legacy's `get_raw_admin_config()` returns (the inner config, not the wrapper)\n\n## Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n\n## Completion\n- Commit with message: `feat: port admin config CRUD with GCS persistence`\n- Report: files changed, verification result\n","numLines":133,"startLine":1,"totalLines":133}}}
